benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request scenarios: TC01, TC02, TC03 cover successful PUT with required headers and valid body.
Non-Existing Resource: TC05 covers 404 for non-existent bundle.
Input Validation and Error Handling: TC04, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC12 cover invalid IDs, headers, malformed/missing body, extra fields, and SQL injection.
Authorization/Access Control: TC06 (missing header) and TC10 (unauthorized) cover authentication/authorization paths.
Edge Case coverage: TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16 cover max items/length, empty value, and unusual URL parameters.
Performance coverage: TC17 and TC18 cover normal and peak load scenarios.
State Variation, Recovery and Integration: TC22-23-24 cover state variations; TC21 recovery; TC20 integration with dependent service.
Regression and Security: TC19 (regression) and TC12 (special characters) cover regression/security aspects.
gaps: Concurrency: no tests for concurrent PUT requests to the same bundle (race conditions).
Rate limiting: no tests for throttling or rate limit policies.
Caching: no tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or caching behavior on PUT.
Partial update rejection: no explicit test verifying rejection of partial updates if PUT semantics require full replacement.
recommendations: Add concurrency tests to validate race conditions with simultaneous PUT requests to the same bundle.
Add rate limiting tests to verify throttling behavior and 429 responses where applicable.
Add caching behavior tests for ETag and Cache-Control headers on PUT responses.
Add explicit tests for partial update rejection if the API does not support partial updates; ensure alignment with PUT semantics.
Include tests for authorization edge cases, e.g., 403 responses for insufficient permissions if applicable.
